      <body>
         <div>
            <head>Translated parts</head>
            <p xml:id="KR1d0052-start">
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-5a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-12T23:58:09.073+09:00">that is the essence of ritual propriety.</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-6a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-13T00:16:43.48+09:00">                                    5. 13. The course (of duty), virtue, benevolence and righteousness</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-6a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-13T03:20:25.569+09:00">polite so as to show up the virtues of ritual propriety</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-6a.29" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-13T03:51:01.764+09:00">Now wild animals have no sense of ritual propriety,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-6a.30" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-13T03:51:07.996+09:00">and so father and son will both go for the same doe. THESE TWO LINES WERE MISSING</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-7a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="chris" modified="2020-03-11T18:55:08.971+09:00">ritual must be studied.</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-14a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-17T17:57:44.544+09:00">CH and he will not own private property.</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-17a.23" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-18T17:25:46.077+09:00">CH: When the superior is by the western stairs</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-18a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-18T17:28:26.109+09:00">                                    7. 31. Outside the curtain or screen (a visitor) should not walk with the formal hasty steps,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-19a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-18T19:26:53.102+09:00">                                    1.2. He carries the (elder's) mat in his arms like the cross-beam of a shadoof.??????</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-19a.29" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-18T21:14:20.719+09:00">                                    so that the bottom of it may be a cubit from the ground.</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-19a.28" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-18T21:14:16.684+09:00">With his two hands he should hold up his lower garment,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-19a.34" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-18T21:31:48.233+09:00">LINE MISSING</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-19a.46" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-18T21:44:23.169+09:00">CH: and refer to the early kings</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-19a.48" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-18T21:51:13.953+09:00">                                    and the teacher puts a question,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-20a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-19T02:44:15.263+09:00">                                    'I wish, when you have a little leisure 閒,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-22a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-19T18:50:35.915+09:00">nor let the lower garment be held up (even) in hot weather.</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-6a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-22T04:30:54.372+09:00">CH: without reference to ritual.</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-6a.27" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-22T04:32:00.215+09:00">even if he can speak,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-6a.28" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-22T04:32:22.735+09:00">                                    does he not have the heart of a brute?</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-8a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-22T04:33:13.092+09:00">CH: then their minds are not fearful.</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-7a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-22T04:33:51.621+09:00">to understand that they are different from beasts.</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-7a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-22T04:33:55.037+09:00">                                    that is contrary to proprity;</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-9a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-22T04:34:57.326+09:00">he will report according the the system of administration therein.</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-12a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-22T04:38:43.566+09:00">this is the conduct of a filial son.</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-13a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-22T04:40:05.447+09:00">CH: then the senior person must sit on a separate mat.</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-19a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-22T04:42:08.14+09:00">one should not stand in handing something to somebody sitting.</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-19a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-22T04:43:20.238+09:00">CH: and one moves the basket with the opening facing oneself.</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-23a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-22T04:45:12.079+09:00">CH: and bowing pick up.</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-24a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-22T05:02:20.499+09:00">Father and son do not share the same mat.</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-24a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-22T05:03:31.982+09:00">                                    having got married, returns home (on a visit),</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-25a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-22T21:02:58.755+09:00">                                    7. 40. When one congratulates (a friend) on his marrying,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-25a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-23T01:12:50.615+09:00">he must avoid befriending him.</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-24a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-23T01:23:00.414+09:00">                                    no (male) enters the door of her apartment.</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-28a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-10-24T05:33:58.467+09:00">                                    is capped, and receives his appellation.</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_043-1a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-12-13T23:24:03.025+09:00">                                    2. The ancients who wished to illustrate illustrious virtue throughout the kingdom,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_006-11a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="chris" modified="2020-02-28T16:30:17.59+09:00">nor any extinction of the principles of earth;</seg>
            <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_001-7a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="chris" modified="2020-03-11T18:55:01.129+09:00">Hence there is the saying,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR1d0052_tls_019-5a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-29T04:37:08.975+09:00">these are what one shares with the common people.</seg>
                </p>
         </div>
